{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.44",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 44,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 44 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:1",
      "text": "We have heard with our ears, O God, our fathers have told us, what deeds thou didst perform in their days, in the days of old:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:2",
      "text": "thou with thy own hand didst drive out the nations, but them thou didst plant; thou didst afflict the peoples, but them thou didst set free;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:3",
      "text": "for not by their own sword did they win the land, nor did their own arm give them victory; but thy right hand, and thy arm, and the light of thy countenance; for thou didst delight in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:4",
      "text": "Thou art my King and my God, who ordainest victories for Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:5",
      "text": "Through thee we push down our foes; through thy name we tread down our assailants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:6",
      "text": "For not in my bow do I trust, nor can my sword save me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:7",
      "text": "But thou hast saved us from our foes, and hast put to confusion those who hate us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:8",
      "text": "In God we have boasted continually, and we will give thanks to thy name for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:9",
      "text": "Yet thou hast cast us off and abased us, and hast not gone out with our armies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:10",
      "text": "Thou hast made us turn back from the foe; and our enemies have gotten spoil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:11",
      "text": "Thou hast made us like sheep for slaughter, and hast scattered us among the nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:12",
      "text": "Thou hast sold thy people for a trifle, demanding no high price for them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:13",
      "text": "Thou hast made us the taunt of our neighbors, the derision and scorn of those about us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:14",
      "text": "Thou hast made us a byword among the nations, a laughingstock among the peoples.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:15",
      "text": "All day long my disgrace is before me, and shame has covered my face,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:16",
      "text": "at the words of the taunters and revilers, at the sight of the enemy and the avenger.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:17",
      "text": "All this has come upon us, though we have not forgotten thee, or been false to thy covenant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:18",
      "text": "Our heart has not turned back, nor have our steps departed from thy way,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:19",
      "text": "that thou shouldst have broken us in the place of jackals, and covered us with deep darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:20",
      "text": "If we had forgotten the name of our God, or spread forth our hands to a strange god,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:21",
      "text": "would not God discover this? For he knows the secrets of the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:22",
      "text": "Nay, for thy sake we are slain all the day long, and accounted as sheep for the slaughter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:23",
      "text": "Rouse thyself! Why sleepest thou, O Lord? Awake! Do not cast us off for ever!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:24",
      "text": "Why dost thou hide thy face? Why dost thou forget our affliction and oppression?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:25",
      "text": "For our soul is bowed down to the dust; our body cleaves to the ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.44.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 44,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 44:26",
      "text": "Rise up, come to our help! Deliver us for the sake of thy steadfast love!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
